issues.suggested_fix:
Provide dependency injection in the template PersonService to match the solution. For example, add a constructor taking PersonRepository and assign it to the field (constructor-based injection), or annotate the field with @Autowired. Example fix:

public PersonService(PersonRepository personRepository) {
    this.personRepository = personRepository;
}

This preserves the intended exercise (students implement the business methods) while ensuring the template compiles and tests can run without students needing to first wire the repository.
